I'll try to destroy you.

19:06.360 --> 19:09.603
REMO: I used to be like you.
The boss loved me.

19:10.120 --> 19:11.690
Gave me a chance
to step up.

19:12.960 --> 19:14.564
Yeah.

19:15.360 --> 19:16.691
What happened?

19:17.320 --> 19:19.800
I don't have
leadership potential.

19:22.040 --> 19:23.530
What'd you do?

19:24.640 --> 19:27.769
I'm not what you would call
consistently reliable.

19:29.640 --> 19:31.768
Now nobody respects me.
Nobody.

19:34.440 --> 19:36.249
You say you've been working
for Gil for 23 years?

19:36.360 --> 19:38.442
Yep. No, not Gil.

19:39.480 --> 19:40.925
Big boss.

19:41.600 --> 19:42.726
Who's that?

19:44.760 --> 19:46.285
You'll know when
you need to know.

19:51.840 --> 19:53.604
Why do you stay?
What?

19:54.360 --> 19:55.771
I mean, if you don't like
it, then why do you stay?

19:56.360 --> 19:57.885
If no one respects you,
why don't you quit?

19:57.960 --> 19:59.291
(CHUCKLES)

19:59.520 --> 20:01.602
Quit? Oh, no,
no, no, no.

20:01.720 --> 20:02.960
There's no quitting
in this job.

20:03.960 --> 20:05.883
No, you can't quit. No.

20:06.480 --> 20:08.005
You could get fired, though.

20:09.680 --> 20:11.967
You don't want that to
happen to you, believe me.

20:13.560 --> 20:15.642
Anyway, good night.

20:41.480 --> 20:42.925
Mother.

20:44.000 --> 20:46.446
I'm sorry, you know, about
what happened at school.

20:47.400 --> 20:49.801
(INHALES)
What did happen?

20:50.320 --> 20:51.765
Well, I got upset.

20:51.840 --> 20:53.683
About what? I don't
want to talk about it.

20:56.760 --> 20:58.569
You know, I promise
it won't happen again.

20:59.240 --> 21:00.685
It can't happen.

21:01.120 --> 21:03.248
Because now they want
you to go see a therapist.

21:03.360 --> 21:04.521
I mean, this is all gonna
go on your record.

21:04.640 --> 21:06.369
You have to be
more careful.

21:07.440 --> 21:09.090
You have to try
to fit in, Norman.

21:09.160 --> 21:11.606
You can't go around being
so emotional all the time.

21:11.680 --> 21:13.523
I know, mother,
and I'm sorry.

21:16.000 --> 21:17.445
But I do think I fit in,

21:18.200 --> 21:19.531
for the most part.

21:23.560 --> 21:25.528
Oh, can you give me a
ride to Emma's shop?

21:25.960 --> 21:27.007
Yeah, why?

21:27.080 --> 21:29.845
I'm working with her dad. He's
teaching me how to do taxidermy.

21:47.200 --> 21:49.521
Will, this is my mom.

21:52.200 --> 21:53.486
I'm Norma Bates.

21:53.560 --> 21:54.925
You can call me Will.

21:55.040 --> 21:58.408
Will, I'm wondering if we
could have a word in private.

21:59.000 --> 22:00.445
Yeah, of course.

22:00.520 --> 22:02.727
Norman, would you
give us a minute, please?

22:03.000 --> 22:04.081
Mmm.

22:11.920 --> 22:13.001
Please.

22:13.080 --> 22:14.525
Thank you.

22:26.280 --> 22:28.760
I don't know if this is such a
good thing for Norman to be doing.

22:30.000 --> 22:31.206
No?
Mmm.

22:31.440 --> 22:33.442
He's already sort of...

22:37.680 --> 22:39.967
(SOFTLY) Sort of
an unusual boy.

22:41.480 --> 22:43.562
You know, he has
a hard time fitting in.

22:43.640 --> 22:45.290
He gets upset very easily.

22:45.360 --> 22:46.486
Really?
Yeah.

22:46.560 --> 22:49.006
He's always very calm
when he's here working.

22:49.080 --> 22:50.241
But hobbies
can be good that way.

22:50.520 --> 22:51.806
Oh, of course.

22:53.480 --> 22:55.960
I just don't want him getting
labeled as a freak or anything.

22:57.160 --> 22:59.731
And I don't think that
learning taxidermy

22:59.800 --> 23:01.290
necessarily makes one
a freak.

23:01.480 --> 23:03.926
No! No, no. I'm not saying
that you're a freak.

23:04.000 --> 23:06.401
No, that's not what I'm saying at all.
Not at all.

23:06.480 --> 23:07.925
Uh-huh.

23:08.000 --> 23:09.650
I'm... (LAUGHS)
I'm not saying that.

23:09.760 --> 23:11.489
Oh, no.
Um...

23:14.120 --> 23:16.487
I'm... I'm just saying that
not a lot of people do it.

23:18.560 --> 23:21.962
Not many people write poetry, but
we still have to have poets, right?

23:23.360 --> 23:25.806
He's good at it,
and he's good company.

23:27.280 --> 23:30.011
We're not hurting anyone.
The animals are already dead.

23:31.120 --> 23:34.488
So what's the harm in letting a
young person follow their passion?

23:35.400 --> 23:36.686
What can go wrong
with that?

23:48.320 --> 23:50.004
Ugh. There he is.

23:50.320 --> 23:51.446
(BRAKES SQUEAL)

23:51.520 --> 23:52.760
Let's go.

23:54.480 --> 23:55.845
DYLAN: You guys heading out
to White Pine Bay?

23:56.000 --> 23:57.525
What does it
look like, douchebag?

23:58.200 --> 23:59.565
You're an hour late,
by the way.

24:05.520 --> 24:06.931
Hey-

24:08.240 --> 24:10.163
That guy right there,

24:10.520 --> 24:11.965
I remember him
from last year.

24:12.040 --> 24:13.371
He's a complete
pain in the ass.

24:13.440 --> 24:14.885
We should
leave him behind.

24:16.280 --> 24:17.884
Gil said we should
bring all of them.

24:17.960 --> 24:19.291
I think
we should do that.

24:20.800 --> 24:22.245
Whatever.

24:23.880 --> 24:26.247
NORMAN: (CHUCKLES)
You're so good at this.

24:26.360 --> 24:27.521
Have you done it
your whole life?

24:27.600 --> 24:29.329
WILL: Pretty much, yeah.

24:29.400 --> 24:32.085
I stopped for about 10 years,
though, when I was married.

24:33.200 --> 24:35.168
Yeah, Emma's mom
didn't like it much.

24:35.920 --> 24:37.843
Didn't like me
very much either.

24:39.280 --> 24:41.248
But I rediscovered myself
after she left.

24:42.080 --> 24:43.127
I'm sorry, Will.

24:46.400 --> 24:47.640
It's okay.

24:48.320 --> 24:50.482
I left that life behind,
in England.

24:52.760 --> 24:55.286
And I got Emma.
So that's all that matters.

25:20.720 --> 25:22.051
(CAR ENGINE RUNNING)

27:11.520 --> 27:12.760
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

27:12.880 --> 27:13.961
(DOOR CREAKS)

28:11.400 --> 28:13.243
(TIRES SCREECH)
(GASPS)

28:14.360 --> 28:15.486
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

28:18.120 --> 28:19.246
What are you
doing here, Norma?

28:21.120 --> 28:22.326
I could ask you
the same thing.

28:23.480 --> 28:25.005
I think
you're following me.

28:26.160 --> 28:28.162
I think you want to know
what I'm up to.

28:30.240 --> 28:32.049
I think you know
what I'm looking for.

28:35.000 --> 28:36.684
I don't know
what you're talking about.

28:36.760 --> 28:38.330
Really?
(KEYS JANGLE)

28:42.120 --> 28:43.690
Nothing at all?

28:45.600 --> 28:46.647
Where is it?

28:49.160 --> 28:51.049
Where is what?
Where'd you hide it?

28:52.040 --> 28:53.326
Hide what?
I don't have anything.

28:54.440 --> 28:55.521
Really?

28:56.160 --> 29:00.006
Then you weren't...
screwing Zack Shelby either?

29:03.840 --> 29:05.205
Excuse me.
I have to go.

29:09.760 --> 29:11.842
Do you think I'm just gonna
walk away from this?

29:14.680 --> 29:17.081
I'm not some moron
like Keith Summers.

29:18.480 --> 29:20.448
He was the bottom rung.
I'm on the top.

29:21.480 --> 29:23.642
You understand?
No, I don't.

29:23.720 --> 29:26.291
I don't understand. I have no
idea what you're talking about.

29:26.360 --> 29:28.966
Well, my guess is, once you think
about it, you'll remember.

29:34.360 --> 29:36.328
When you do,
come by my hotel room.

29:36.760 --> 29:40.003
Mmm. We'll talk
about it. Okay?

29:54.480 --> 29:57.245
Tell me a little bit about
losing your father, Norman.

30:02.440 --> 30:04.522
He died in an accident
in our garage.

30:04.600 --> 30:07.843
NORMA: Six months ago. It
was devastating, of course.

30:09.160 --> 30:12.130
But we moved,

30:12.960 --> 30:15.930
and we're doing our best to start
over and reinvent our lives.

30:17.320 --> 30:18.560
Yes.

30:23.360 --> 30:26.921
Can you talk to me about
how it felt to move

30:27.360 --> 30:30.682
from the home where you lived with
your dad to a whole new town?

30:30.840 --> 30:34.447
Yeah. (CLEARS THROAT) Yeah,
I guess it, uh, it felt...

30:35.760 --> 30:37.250
I guess I felt
a lot of things.

30:40.920 --> 30:42.524
Like what, Norman?

30:42.960 --> 30:45.850
It was sad. He was sad.
We were both sad.

30:46.280 --> 30:47.486
Mmm, sad.

30:50.080 --> 30:51.366
(SIGHS)

30:51.440 --> 30:55.729
XANDER: (SINGING)
<i>In the dark night</i>

30:56.440 --> 30:58.886
<i>I found all your love</i>

30:59.400 --> 31:00.970
(LAUGHS)

31:04.160 --> 31:09.610
<i>You were an angel sent
from above I thought...</i>

31:09.720 --> 31:11.210
Could you
just shut up?

31:13.400 --> 31:14.481
Put that guitar away.

31:15.640 --> 31:18.371
My head is about
to explode.

31:18.480 --> 31:19.970
I can't listen
to any more of his crap.

31:20.960 --> 31:23.930
XANDER: You all remember this
pus ball from last year, right?

31:25.120 --> 31:27.691
I think I'm gonna tell Gil we're
not coming back next year.

31:30.400 --> 31:31.925
And it's past lunch.

31:32.000 --> 31:33.889
It's time for you to pull
over and buy us a meal.

31:33.960 --> 31:35.200
We'll stop in a while.

31:36.320 --> 31:39.324
Management here seems to think he
can tell us when we're gonna eat.

31:40.640 --> 31:43.803
We want to stop, man!
We want to stop.

31:43.960 --> 31:45.007
Remo, pull over.

31:55.320 --> 31:56.606
Get out.

31:57.600 --> 31:59.682
Get out and what? You want
me to watch you piss?

32:00.680 --> 32:03.251
No, I want you to get out
of the van right now.

32:04.520 --> 32:06.090
You, your guitar,

32:06.160 --> 32:09.801
and anyone else who thinks this is
a democracy, you can get out, too!

32:12.000 --> 32:14.526
Stop for lunch whenever, man.
It's all good.

32:14.800 --> 32:16.131
I said get out!

32:18.920 --> 32:20.206
Let's go!

32:23.960 --> 32:26.691
Walk over here. Go on.

32:45.200 --> 32:46.565
Thank you.

32:47.480 --> 32:49.448
So same time
next week, Norman?

32:50.600 --> 32:53.490
Well, I'm gonna call
and schedule something,

32:53.560 --> 32:57.531
but we have a lot going on
with the motel opening.

32:59.400 --> 33:01.607
May I talk to you
privately for a moment?

33:04.080 --> 33:06.686
Mmm, yeah. Yeah, I'll
be right out, Norman.

33:19.200 --> 33:20.406
Um...

33:22.080 --> 33:25.687
I think it might be helpful if I
saw Norman on his own next time.

33:26.960 --> 33:29.566
No offense, but I don't
feel comfortable with that.

33:31.080 --> 33:32.605
I mean,
I don't know you.

33:35.760 --> 33:38.127
Have you ever been
in therapy, Mrs. Bates?

33:40.560 --> 33:41.800
No.

33:42.720 --> 33:45.690
Would you consider coming for
some sessions of your own?

33:47.280 --> 33:48.566
Why?

33:48.720 --> 33:51.007
Well, I've noticed

33:51.080 --> 33:53.481
you have a strong
influence on Norman,

33:54.280 --> 33:56.123
maybe a need
to control things.

33:57.680 --> 33:59.170
I'm his mother.
(CHUCKLES)

33:59.440 --> 34:00.805
Of course.

34:00.880 --> 34:03.690
But as our children grow older,
we need to let go a little.

34:04.120 --> 34:05.531
Hmm?

34:07.000 --> 34:08.570
The thing is, um...

34:09.719 --> 34:13.327
People who feel the need
to control everything

34:13.800 --> 34:17.521
often, in actuality, feel out
of control on the inside.

34:19.360 --> 34:20.646
Do you ever
feel that way?

34:20.800 --> 34:22.370
(INHALES SHARPLY)

34:25.320 --> 34:27.527
No, I don't.

34:29.199 --> 34:30.610
(STUTTERS)

34:32.199 --> 34:35.522
I feel completely in control
of everything in my life.

34:36.960 --> 34:39.884
How dare you make these
stupid assumptions about me.

34:39.960 --> 34:41.724
You don't know
anything about me.

34:42.159 --> 34:44.128
I work hard.
I take care of my son.

34:44.480 --> 34:46.208
I know what's right and
what's wrong for him.

34:46.280 --> 34:48.282
No one pushes me around.
I control my own life.

34:48.360 --> 34:50.931
I'm in total control of my own life.
I have a lot going on.

34:51.000 --> 34:52.081
I have a lot to deal with,

34:52.159 --> 34:55.130
but I do not
feel powerless, ever!

34:57.720 --> 34:58.846
(SIGHS)
We're going, Norman.

34:58.920 --> 35:00.763
What happened, Mother?
Did I say something wrong?

35:00.840 --> 35:02.490
No, you were perfect.
Let's go.

35:15.520 --> 35:18.000
Norman, go up to the house.
I'll be right there.

35:19.200 --> 35:20.770
Okay, Mom.

35:31.600 --> 35:32.931
Come on in.

35:33.600 --> 35:37.127
I'd offer you a drink, but I
can't seem to find a mini bar.

35:37.600 --> 35:40.888
Here's your money back.
I want you out of my motel!

35:43.760 --> 35:44.886
You didn't just
do that, did you?

35:45.000 --> 35:47.731
Look, I don't know who you
are, and I don't care,

35:47.800 --> 35:50.280
but I don't want to have
anything more to do with you.

35:50.520 --> 35:52.921
Okay? We are not having
future business together.

35:53.000 --> 35:55.002
You are not booking rooms
here ever again.

35:55.080 --> 35:56.889
You need to dial it down
right now, Norma,

35:56.960 --> 35:58.291
before I get
truly annoyed.

35:58.880 --> 36:01.963
You want me to call the cops and tell
them what you've been saying to me?

36:02.040 --> 36:06.284
Hmm? How you wanted to rent
rooms and have "privacy"?

36:06.440 --> 36:09.171
How you knew Keith
Summers and Zack Shelby?

36:11.280 --> 36:13.009
I know all about
you and Zack Shelby.

36:18.400 --> 36:19.606
What?
There's nothing to know.

36:24.280 --> 36:25.930
I'm not afraid of you.

36:26.440 --> 36:28.124
You have no power
over me.

36:28.280 --> 36:30.248
You were gonna try and convince
me that you and Shelby

36:30.320 --> 36:33.608
were casual acquaintances, that you
knew nothing about what was going on?

36:37.440 --> 36:41.809
If you are not out of this room in
five minutes, lam calling the police.

36:42.320 --> 36:44.891
Okay. You want to play?

36:46.320 --> 36:47.446
We'll play-

36:47.800 --> 36:49.404
Five minutes!

37:23.840 --> 37:24.887
(ENGINE STARTS)

37:33.640 --> 37:34.846
(TIRES SCREECH)

37:41.120 --> 37:42.406
Hey-

37:46.600 --> 37:49.843
Can we talk?
Mmm, yeah.

37:59.560 --> 38:02.370
The reason I told those
girls about you and Bradley

38:02.440 --> 38:03.965
is because I heard them
talking about you,

38:05.200 --> 38:06.725
saying things like,

38:06.880 --> 38:10.168
it was embarrassing how you just
stared at Bradley all the time

38:10.240 --> 38:11.890
and how someone like her

38:11.960 --> 38:14.008
would never have anything to
do with someone like you.

38:18.200 --> 38:19.201
Oh.

38:19.680 --> 38:21.569
And it just made me
so angry,

38:22.760 --> 38:25.081
because I think
you are so special

38:25.160 --> 38:26.924
and so much better
than any of them.

38:29.560 --> 38:30.925
I just couldn't keep
my mouth shut.

38:33.280 --> 38:34.725
Anyway, I'm sorry.

38:35.880 --> 38:37.882
I just didn't want you to
think I had any other motive.

38:46.040 --> 38:47.610
I know you think
I like you.

38:48.560 --> 38:51.291
And, okay,
I guess I do, but...

38:54.600 --> 38:55.601
It's not about that.

38:57.600 --> 39:00.410
I don't care if you're not
gonna be my boyfriend.

39:01.920 --> 39:05.049
I'm pretty used to things not
turning out the way I expect

39:05.120 --> 39:06.201
and making the best of it.

39:08.600 --> 39:09.965
It's just...

39:12.120 --> 39:14.521
You are really
special to me.

39:16.160 --> 39:17.730
And I feel safe with you.

39:23.280 --> 39:24.611
You are my friend,

39:27.280 --> 39:30.727
and I don't want to
mess that up or lose you.

39:36.680 --> 39:38.284
I don't have
many real friends.

39:39.680 --> 39:41.045
(CHUCKLES)

39:45.080 --> 39:46.320
It's okay, Emma.

39:49.880 --> 39:51.644
I'm sorry I was mad.

40:01.640 --> 40:03.483
I'm... I'm sorry. If there was
a door, I would have knocked.

40:04.880 --> 40:06.450
It's fine, Dad.
(CHUCKLES)

40:34.720 --> 40:36.563
How many rooms
we got available?

40:36.640 --> 40:39.211
All of them.
12 rooms, 12 vacancies.

40:42.200 --> 40:43.804
What happened
to number nine?

40:44.360 --> 40:47.523
You were right about that guy.
So I got rid of him.

40:47.920 --> 40:49.001
I handled it.

40:50.640 --> 40:52.722
Cool. Um...

40:53.600 --> 40:55.887
Look, I got seven people
here who need rooms.

40:56.280 --> 40:57.520
They're gonna be doing
some work for my boss,

40:57.680 --> 40:59.967
and we need somewhere to put
'em for the next two weeks.

41:00.040 --> 41:01.246
Really?

41:02.920 --> 41:05.810
Yeah! Yeah. Well, I'll
go open the office.

41:07.560 --> 41:08.800
Thank you, Dylan.

41:10.120 --> 41:11.770
Yeah, sure, Norma.

41:19.080 --> 41:22.448
You know, Norman is staying
for dinner at Emma's tonight.

41:22.880 --> 41:24.166
Do you want to go get a
bite in the village?

41:24.240 --> 41:26.049
It would just be
the two of us.

41:27.480 --> 41:29.289
Yeah.
Yeah?

41:29.360 --> 41:31.522
Yeah, sure. Okay.

41:32.280 --> 41:34.931
Okay. I'm just gonna
get out of these clothes.

41:35.000 --> 41:37.241
I'll run upstairs, and then
I'll come back down to meet you

41:37.320 --> 41:39.800
and settle everybody in.
Okay?

41:40.240 --> 41:41.446
Okay-

41:41.840 --> 41:43.604
(CHUCKLES) Okay.

42:09.440 --> 42:11.966
On! (SCREAMS)

42:12.240 --> 42:13.321
Oh, God!

42:13.400 --> 42:15.880
Norman! Norman!

42:16.440 --> 42:17.851
(SCREAMS)

42:18.640 --> 42:19.971
Norman! Norman!

